WEBVTT

00:01.401 --> 00:04.303
You will go out with your son
tomorrow morning at 10:00.

00:04.305 --> 00:05.804
Buy some gas with a credit card.
Go to Starbucks.

00:05.806 --> 00:08.307
Establish a record of you
not being in your house

00:08.309 --> 00:09.808
between 10:00 and noon.

00:09.810 --> 00:12.344
You're going to find Daphne
on the floor beside the sink,

00:12.346 --> 00:14.480
neck broken like she slipped
getting out of the shower.

00:14.482 --> 00:16.382
There's a man
coming here to kill you.

00:18.385 --> 00:20.152
You're not an English teacher.

00:20.154 --> 00:21.687
When I was young,
watching movies,

00:21.689 --> 00:23.155
I always thought
it was so stupid

00:23.157 --> 00:24.823
when they dump a body
in the river.

00:24.825 --> 00:27.559
I thought, "Why don't they make
a friend at a funeral home

00:27.561 --> 00:28.994
and cremate the body?"

00:28.996 --> 00:31.864
I got a call from
- Your brother David last week.

00:31.866 --> 00:33.298
He left a message.

00:33.300 --> 00:35.334
All he said was
- He was returning your call.

00:35.336 --> 00:37.169
I called him five years ago.

00:37.171 --> 00:39.038
So he's called
three times?
- Yeah.

00:39.040 --> 00:40.406
You think Ava knows what's up?

00:40.408 --> 00:42.674
Hey!
- Hey, Uncle Jav!

00:42.676 --> 00:44.510
Daniela: Has he cooked for you?
Not yet.

00:44.512 --> 00:46.745
You're a private chef,
Uncle Jav.

00:46.747 --> 00:48.547
A private chef?

01:06.933 --> 01:08.367
I'm starving.

01:08.369 --> 01:10.335
You just had a Big Mac
an hour ago.

01:10.337 --> 01:12.171
Gross. No, I didn't.

01:12.173 --> 01:13.572
Yes, you did.

01:13.574 --> 01:16.442
I had a double cheeseburger.
There's a difference.

01:16.444 --> 01:18.010
Well, the point is
you ate food.

01:18.012 --> 01:20.879
Now I want to eat again.

01:20.881 --> 01:23.282
There's something
wrong with you.

01:23.284 --> 01:25.050
Would you please just
find a place?

01:25.052 --> 01:27.286
I have to concentrate.

01:27.288 --> 01:29.021
I found a place.

01:31.458 --> 01:33.592
This is a shopping mall.

01:33.594 --> 01:35.527
This is a shopping mall.

01:35.529 --> 01:37.729
I don't need clothes.
I need food

01:37.731 --> 01:40.599
Well, at shopping malls, you can
get both of those things.

01:40.601 --> 01:42.601
Here.

01:42.603 --> 01:43.769
What is happening?

01:43.771 --> 01:45.370
You're going shopping.
- Why?

01:45.372 --> 01:47.573
Because you like
going shopping.

01:47.575 --> 01:48.907
Because we're going
to my family dinner,

01:48.909 --> 01:50.542
and maybe you want
something new to wear.

01:50.544 --> 01:52.044
I have something new to wear.

01:52.046 --> 01:54.046
Yeah, something you stole.

01:54.048 --> 01:55.848
How would you know that?

01:58.051 --> 01:59.618
Why do you care?

01:59.620 --> 02:00.953
Because when you are
with my family,

02:00.955 --> 02:02.588
I want you to wear
something you bought,

02:02.590 --> 02:04.490
not something you stole
from an innocent person.

02:04.492 --> 02:06.792
There is a difference.
Oh, my God.

02:06.794 --> 02:09.161
Do we need to keep arguing,
or do you want to take this

02:09.163 --> 02:11.530
and go buy things with it?

02:15.401 --> 02:17.102
[ Sighs ]

02:17.104 --> 02:18.403
You're not coming with me.

02:18.405 --> 02:19.938
Didn't say I was
coming with you.

02:19.940 --> 02:22.141
You don't get
wardrobe approval.

02:22.143 --> 02:25.244
Okay.

02:25.246 --> 02:26.979
[ Car door closes ]

02:38.158 --> 02:42.060
♪♪

02:47.834 --> 02:50.302
♪ I hear you through the walls ♪

02:50.304 --> 02:53.872
♪ Now I can never leave ♪

02:55.975 --> 02:58.443
♪ I guess you're taking care ♪

02:58.445 --> 03:01.046
♪ Of your dirty laundry ♪

03:25.805 --> 03:28.807
Hey, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, what's...?

03:31.678 --> 03:33.478
What are you doing here?

03:33.480 --> 03:34.846
What do you mean?

03:34.848 --> 03:37.649
I told you to park in
the third spot from the end.

03:37.651 --> 03:41.086
This is the...
One, two, three...

03:41.088 --> 03:43.255
Four, it's fine.

03:43.257 --> 03:45.023
[ Sighs ]

03:45.025 --> 03:46.658
Unlock it.

03:52.265 --> 03:53.832
Turn off the car.

03:53.834 --> 03:56.101
Why? I thought we would
go for a drive.

03:56.103 --> 03:57.202
We're not driving anywhere.

03:57.204 --> 04:00.205
Turn off the car.

04:00.207 --> 04:02.774
[ Keys click, engine shuts off ]

04:02.776 --> 04:03.875
Why are you wearing gloves?

04:03.877 --> 04:06.912
Because I am sitting
in your car.

04:06.914 --> 04:08.914
Yeah, but we're just talking.

04:08.916 --> 04:11.516
No,<i> you're</i> just talking.

04:11.518 --> 04:12.551
What?

04:12.553 --> 04:13.885
I did my job.

04:13.887 --> 04:15.854
It's over.
We don't need to talk.

04:15.856 --> 04:20.292
You sent me a text eight hours
ago and said you needed to talk.

04:20.294 --> 04:22.561
So you're just talking.

04:22.563 --> 04:24.263
But why are you wearing
those gloves?

04:24.265 --> 04:26.632
I don't like germs.

04:29.302 --> 04:32.871
Um, okay.

04:32.873 --> 04:36.808
Look, the police are asking me
all kinds of questions.

04:36.810 --> 04:38.777
Of course they are.
You killed your wife.

04:38.779 --> 04:41.913
<i>You</i> killed my wife.

04:41.915 --> 04:44.383
No, you paid me
to kill your wife.

04:44.385 --> 04:47.386
So<i> you</i> killed your wife.

04:47.388 --> 04:50.922
They're asking the same
questions over and over.

04:50.924 --> 04:52.124
The husband is always
the first suspect.

04:52.126 --> 04:54.426
Yeah, but they're
gonna find out.

04:54.428 --> 04:55.661
- No, they won't.
- Yes, they are.

04:55.663 --> 04:57.095
They're gonna find out.

04:57.097 --> 05:00.299
Chase, I told you I am
very good at what I do.

05:00.301 --> 05:02.467
So, if you've been
- Following my instructions,

05:02.469 --> 05:03.468
they will not find out.

05:03.470 --> 05:06.405
I have. I did.

05:06.407 --> 05:09.007
For the most part.

05:11.644 --> 05:14.212
For the most part?

05:16.949 --> 05:18.917
Can I get a room
started for you?

05:18.919 --> 05:21.920
No thanks. I can kind of
tell what'll work on me.

05:21.922 --> 05:24.089
So you're buying all of that?

05:24.091 --> 05:25.624
Yeah. Get excited.

05:25.626 --> 05:27.592
I hope you work on commission.

05:27.594 --> 05:30.462
Uh, well, we do,
but nothing's on sale,

05:30.464 --> 05:32.864
just so you know.

05:32.866 --> 05:36.201
What is this?
"Pretty Woman?"

05:36.203 --> 05:39.171
I told you go to Starbucks
with your son.

05:39.173 --> 05:40.972
I know.

05:40.974 --> 05:43.208
You didn't go to
Starbucks with your son?

05:43.210 --> 05:46.111
He wanted to skateboard.
I took him to the park.

05:46.113 --> 05:47.312
There's these curbs
that he likes.

05:47.314 --> 05:49.481
He does trick on the curbs.

05:49.483 --> 05:51.550
Were any of his friends there?

05:51.552 --> 05:52.684
No.

05:52.686 --> 05:54.219
Were any of your friends there?

05:54.221 --> 05:55.821
No. No.

05:55.823 --> 05:57.322
So why would you do that?

05:57.324 --> 05:58.990
I know, okay?

05:58.992 --> 06:01.660
By Tyler was relentless.
He wouldn't shut up.

06:01.662 --> 06:02.994
And... and...
and I was stressed.

06:02.996 --> 06:05.330
You were supposed to
establish a record

06:05.332 --> 06:07.833
of you not being in your house
when Daphne was killed.

06:07.835 --> 06:09.868
I know! I know!

06:09.870 --> 06:13.372
And they know,
- And I don't know what to do

06:13.374 --> 06:14.740
except tell the truth.

06:14.742 --> 06:16.508
You will not that,
or you will die, too.

06:16.510 --> 06:18.143
[ Sighs ]

06:18.145 --> 06:19.511
So would you.

06:19.513 --> 06:21.346
No.

06:21.348 --> 06:22.748
No one would find me.

06:22.750 --> 06:25.384
But you're the one
who did this.

06:25.386 --> 06:28.053
You killed her.

06:28.055 --> 06:30.989
You should be the one
that has to pay.

06:30.991 --> 06:34.393
This is not
how it works, Chase.

06:34.395 --> 06:36.294
[ Sobs ]

06:37.196 --> 06:40.198
I'm a bad person.
I'm a bad person.

06:40.200 --> 06:43.101
I'm a fucking coward.

06:43.103 --> 06:45.337
I can't even
go grocery shopping.

06:45.339 --> 06:46.571
What?

06:46.573 --> 06:48.540
And it's Tyler's
birthday next week.

06:48.542 --> 06:51.576
I don't even know how to plan
for a kid's birthday party.

06:51.578 --> 06:52.878
Daphne used to do that!

06:52.880 --> 06:54.446
We're not talking about
your son's birthday!

06:54.448 --> 06:56.047
Yes, we are!

06:56.049 --> 06:59.217
We're talking about whatever
I want to talk about, okay?

06:59.219 --> 07:00.419
So fuck you!

07:00.421 --> 07:01.887
Calm down.
- No!

07:01.889 --> 07:04.623
Fuck you for ruining my life!

07:04.625 --> 07:08.894
For ruining my son's life!

07:08.896 --> 07:10.395
For killing Daphne.

07:10.397 --> 07:13.432
You didn't have to do it.
You could have said no.

07:13.434 --> 07:14.633
I am very sorry I didn't.

07:14.635 --> 07:17.469
You should have.
You did that to her.

07:17.471 --> 07:19.704
I didn't.

07:24.043 --> 07:27.078
What are you doing, Chase?

07:27.080 --> 07:30.081
I'll feel better
if you're dead.

07:30.083 --> 07:33.118
I'll feel better this way.

07:34.120 --> 07:35.787
[ Gunshot ]

07:35.789 --> 07:37.422
[ Birds chirping ]

07:37.424 --> 07:40.459
[ Panting ]

08:06.419 --> 08:10.322
♪♪

08:12.458 --> 08:13.959
[ Knock on door ]

08:13.961 --> 08:16.194
Carol: How's everything
going in there?

08:16.196 --> 08:18.763
You know what?
You were totally right.

08:18.765 --> 08:21.633
I am so glad
I tried all this on.

08:21.635 --> 08:25.470
Yeah, how crazy would it be if
all of that worked on you?

08:25.472 --> 08:28.173
Really crazy.

08:34.313 --> 08:36.147
None of it worked.

08:36.149 --> 08:37.649
Oh, nothing?

08:37.651 --> 08:38.984
Nope.

08:38.986 --> 08:42.354
And like you said,
none of it was on sale.

08:42.356 --> 08:44.689
Bye, Carol.

08:44.691 --> 08:46.057
Oh.

08:55.801 --> 08:59.905
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

09:13.986 --> 09:15.520
[ Siren chirps ]

09:15.522 --> 09:17.889
[ Radio chatter ]

09:26.999 --> 09:30.435
You're going to find Daphne
on the floor beside the sink.

09:30.437 --> 09:33.705
Neck broken like she slipped
getting out of the shower.

09:33.707 --> 09:36.608
It happens all the time.

09:36.610 --> 09:41.179
Officer: Ma'am? Ma'am?
I need you to step away, okay?

09:41.181 --> 09:43.748
I need all of you to step away.

09:43.750 --> 09:47.852
[ Indistinct talking ]

10:07.440 --> 10:08.773
I can explain.

10:08.775 --> 10:11.242
Please don't.

10:11.244 --> 10:13.244
Perfect.

10:13.246 --> 10:15.880
♪ Hard time forgiving ♪

10:15.882 --> 10:18.650
♪ Even harder forgetting ♪

10:18.652 --> 10:20.819
♪ Before you do something ♪

10:20.821 --> 10:23.254
♪ You might regret, friend ♪

10:23.256 --> 10:26.091
♪ Bricks are caving in ♪

10:26.093 --> 10:28.259
♪ Oh, how sweet this sin ♪

10:28.261 --> 10:31.096
♪ I left you the keys ♪

10:31.098 --> 10:33.264
♪ You won't let me in ♪

10:33.266 --> 10:35.834
♪ Hard time forgiving ♪

10:35.836 --> 10:38.436
♪ Even harder forgetting ♪

10:38.438 --> 10:40.905
♪ Before you do something ♪

10:40.907 --> 10:44.442
♪ You might regret, friend ♪

10:44.444 --> 10:46.411
♪♪

10:46.413 --> 10:47.979
♪ Like a river ♪

10:47.981 --> 10:50.415
♪ Like a river, sh... ♪

10:50.417 --> 10:52.317
♪ Like a river ♪

10:52.319 --> 10:53.952
♪ Like a river, sh... ♪
[ Thump ]

10:53.954 --> 10:55.954
♪ Like a river ♪

10:55.956 --> 10:57.422
♪ Like a river ♪

10:57.424 --> 11:01.359
♪ Shut your mouth
and run me like a river ♪

11:01.361 --> 11:05.096
♪ How do you fall in love ♪

11:05.098 --> 11:08.933
♪ Harder than a bullet
could hit you? ♪

11:08.935 --> 11:12.537
♪ How do you fall apart ♪

11:12.539 --> 11:15.540
♪ Faster
than a hairpin trigger? ♪

11:15.542 --> 11:20.011
♪ Don't you say,
don't you say it ♪

11:20.013 --> 11:23.648
♪ Don't say, don't you say it ♪

11:23.650 --> 11:27.552
♪ One breath,
and it'll just break it ♪

11:27.554 --> 11:32.190
♪ So shut your mouth
and run me like a river ♪

11:32.192 --> 11:34.025
Why aren't
you wearing your wig?

11:34.027 --> 11:35.694
Why would I be wearing a wig?

11:35.696 --> 11:37.962
The long blond one. You were
wearing it when you met Ava.

11:37.964 --> 11:39.831
No, I wasn't.
- Yes, you were.

11:39.833 --> 11:41.299
You're thinking of the selfie.

11:41.301 --> 11:42.667
All week she's been asking

11:42.669 --> 11:44.502
if I was bringing
- My girlfriend Marilyn, so...

11:44.504 --> 11:47.405
Marilyn Monroe?
So she thinks I'm fat?

11:47.407 --> 11:49.040
No.
She thinks you're blond.

11:49.042 --> 11:51.376
Ava knows I wear wigs.

11:51.378 --> 11:54.679
"Marilyn" is only a compliment
if you're already curvy.

11:54.681 --> 11:57.215
If you're skinny, it means
you need to lose weight.

11:57.217 --> 11:58.850
Every woman knows this.

11:58.852 --> 12:00.218
Well, she's from Argentina.

12:00.220 --> 12:01.519
She doesn't have
the same references.

12:01.521 --> 12:04.322
Yes, she does.
- This shit is international.

12:04.324 --> 12:06.024
Besides,
if I wear the blond wig,

12:06.026 --> 12:07.492
I have to do
the Southern accent,

12:07.494 --> 12:09.761
and Ava already knows
I don't have a Southern accent.

12:09.763 --> 12:11.062
So do your nieces.

12:11.064 --> 12:12.564
Why would you have
to do a Southern accent?

12:12.566 --> 12:14.065
Because that's just
the way it works.

12:14.067 --> 12:16.000
What?
- I'm not explaining it.

12:16.002 --> 12:17.202
Fine.

12:17.204 --> 12:18.870
Can you please
make me a Negroni?

12:18.872 --> 12:22.707
Okay, just help me
- To understand why we're here.

12:22.709 --> 12:24.709
When Ava invited me
to your family dinner,

12:24.711 --> 12:27.378
I thought it would be you,
Ava, and the girls.

12:27.380 --> 12:29.214
I didn't realize
- It would also be your parents

12:29.216 --> 12:32.050
who you haven't spoken to
in like 20 years.

12:32.052 --> 12:34.619
[ Sighs ]

12:34.621 --> 12:37.555
My father paid for my sister
to build this restaurant.

12:37.557 --> 12:39.891
Tonight is a celebration
of this achievement.

12:39.893 --> 12:41.893
So they invited you?
After all this time?

12:41.895 --> 12:43.361
Yes.
- Why?

12:43.363 --> 12:45.230
Because my father
had a heart attack,

12:45.232 --> 12:47.398
like I've also told you
64 times.

12:47.400 --> 12:48.733
Yes, but you still
haven't told me

12:48.735 --> 12:50.769
why you haven't spoken
to anyone in your family

12:50.771 --> 12:52.537
since you were 16.

12:52.539 --> 12:54.239
'Cause I don't talk
about that to anyone.

12:54.241 --> 12:55.740
Oh, that's healthy.
[ Knife slams ]

12:55.742 --> 12:58.276
Is it okay
- That you not know something?!

12:58.278 --> 12:59.277
Huh?

12:59.279 --> 13:01.079
What? Why? When? Who?

13:01.081 --> 13:03.615
You harass me with all
the questions all the time.

13:03.617 --> 13:07.085
But some people just don't like
to talk about every single thing

13:07.087 --> 13:09.120
that has ever happened
to them in their life.

13:09.122 --> 13:11.222
I would think
you would understand.

13:11.224 --> 13:13.491
Have I ever asked you
for all the details?

13:13.493 --> 13:15.894
All the horrible shit
you've been through?

13:15.896 --> 13:18.329
Okay, I'm sorry.

13:20.432 --> 13:22.600
Okay.

13:22.602 --> 13:26.437
Now, do you think
you can make me a Negroni

13:26.439 --> 13:29.007
without drinking
- All the gin behind the bar?

13:29.009 --> 13:30.508
Possibly.

13:36.982 --> 13:37.482
♪♪

13:48.761 --> 13:52.163
[ Ice cubes rattling ]

13:52.165 --> 13:54.098
So, who all is coming, exactly?

13:54.100 --> 13:55.667
Javier didn't tell you?

13:55.669 --> 13:57.468
He wasn't specific.

13:57.470 --> 14:00.338
Big surprise.
- So, what?

14:00.340 --> 14:01.639
Your father
had this heart attack

14:01.641 --> 14:04.475
and just decided
he wanted to see Javier

14:04.477 --> 14:06.377
for the first time
since he was a teenager?
[ Door opens ]

14:06.379 --> 14:08.479
Silk: Hello?
- Ah!

14:08.481 --> 14:10.148
[ Laughs ]

14:10.150 --> 14:11.549
Place looks great.

14:11.551 --> 14:13.484
Thank you.

14:13.486 --> 14:14.853
- Hi!
- Hey, Letty!

14:14.855 --> 14:17.355
- Hi!
- Hey.

14:17.656 --> 14:19.290
Ava: Hello?

14:19.292 --> 14:22.560
[ Speaks indistinctly ]
- Oh!

14:22.862 --> 14:24.062
Yeah!

14:24.064 --> 14:27.332
- Oh! Hi, my loves.
- Oh! Mwah!

14:27.334 --> 14:30.368
So, this is yours,
but I want it to be mine.

14:30.370 --> 14:32.203
Yes. And I want it
to be mine.

14:32.205 --> 14:35.306
Babe, you didn't tell me
I'm about to meet 97 people.

14:35.308 --> 14:37.175
Why didn't you tell her
about everyone?

14:37.177 --> 14:38.710
It slipped my mind.

14:38.712 --> 14:40.044
I guess it could be worse.

14:40.046 --> 14:43.681
Last guy I seriously dated...
His family was from Delaware.

14:43.683 --> 14:45.183
And?

14:45.185 --> 14:47.185
That's it.
That's the whole story.

14:47.187 --> 14:48.686
[ Laughter ]

14:48.688 --> 14:50.388
He just got back
from a thing in Nassau.

14:50.390 --> 14:52.657
For what?
- Couple players
on the Atlanta Braves...

14:52.659 --> 14:54.659
wives, private jets,
the whole thing.

14:54.661 --> 14:55.593
[ Sighs ]

14:55.595 --> 14:57.996
Jav, tell them the story
about the...

14:57.998 --> 14:59.931
I don't want to.
[ Sighs ] Fine.

14:59.933 --> 15:05.103
So, okay. So, they wanted
oysters flown in from Maine.

15:05.105 --> 15:07.105
Five years ago,
they're living on a farm

15:07.107 --> 15:08.406
in the Dominican Republic,

15:08.408 --> 15:10.341
and now they need oysters
flown in from Maine?

15:10.343 --> 15:12.710
Look, I need to get
everything done before
everyone arrives, so...

15:12.712 --> 15:15.213
He found this world-famous
oyster supplier,

15:15.215 --> 15:17.448
but what's so crazy is
that she randomly only does

15:17.450 --> 15:18.883
the oyster thing as a hobby.

15:18.885 --> 15:20.184
She's actually a lawyer.

15:20.186 --> 15:22.120
Anyway, he had them
flown in the cargo

15:22.122 --> 15:23.521
of some guy's private jet.

15:23.523 --> 15:26.057
Which, uh, players
were they, again?

15:26.059 --> 15:27.558
Uh, I don't know.

15:27.560 --> 15:29.460
Sports.
[ Laughing ] Who cares?

15:29.462 --> 15:31.529
Upton was one of them, right?

15:31.531 --> 15:32.931
Upton and a couple
of shortstops?

15:32.933 --> 15:34.265
Okay, stop!

15:34.267 --> 15:36.100
Everyone, stop.

15:36.102 --> 15:37.602
I'm sorry, but I need to work.

15:37.604 --> 15:39.437
Everyone is arriving
in 10 minutes, and I ha...

15:39.439 --> 15:42.707
Okay!
Calm down.

15:42.709 --> 15:44.442
We're going.

15:44.444 --> 15:46.945
Silk, can you help me
with the dinner table?

15:46.947 --> 15:49.147
Sure.
- Daniela, Sofia,
help your uncle.

15:49.149 --> 15:51.916
Uh, how?

15:51.918 --> 15:53.251
Like this.

15:53.253 --> 15:55.386
You just start helping.
- Okay. Um...

15:55.388 --> 15:56.955
Thank you.
Be right back.

15:58.223 --> 15:59.991
What?

16:03.295 --> 16:05.296
What the fuck are you doing?

16:05.298 --> 16:07.265
I'm playing along.
No, you're not.

16:07.267 --> 16:09.267
You're screwing around
with bullshit stories.

16:09.269 --> 16:11.436
You're a private chef
with absolutely no stories.

16:11.438 --> 16:13.071
I'm trying to help you.

16:13.073 --> 16:15.073
I'm about to see a lot of people
I haven't seen in many years.

16:15.075 --> 16:17.442
I don't want it fucked up.
This is<i> my</i> family, not yours.

16:17.444 --> 16:18.943
Well, there are no lies
in my family.

16:18.945 --> 16:20.178
They know I'm a thief.

16:20.180 --> 16:21.813
Does your family
know what you do?

16:21.815 --> 16:23.648
Oh, and, P.S.,
if you can cook,

16:23.650 --> 16:26.851
why bother with all that
horrendous philanthropy shit?

16:26.853 --> 16:28.653
Because.
- Because?

16:28.655 --> 16:31.122
Because when you tell different
lies to different people,

16:31.124 --> 16:33.324
when something comes back to me
through a third party,

16:33.326 --> 16:34.792
I know who's talking to who.

16:34.794 --> 16:36.928
A third party?
- Yes.

16:36.930 --> 16:38.830
Seriously?
- Yes.

16:38.832 --> 16:39.998
You don't do that?

16:40.000 --> 16:41.466
No.
- Why not?

16:41.468 --> 16:43.801
Because that would require
time and energy

16:43.803 --> 16:45.803
better spent doing
literally anything else.

16:45.805 --> 16:47.472
Yeah, except
when it's<i> your</i> family.

16:47.474 --> 16:50.008
[ Sighs ]
- Think of a title
for your book.

16:50.010 --> 16:51.776
What book?

16:51.778 --> 16:54.679
You told the girls, who told
my sister, you were a writer.

16:54.681 --> 16:56.314
I told them
I work for Instagram.

16:56.316 --> 16:57.815
You told them
you work for Instagram

16:57.817 --> 16:59.951
to support your true passion,
which is writing.

16:59.953 --> 17:02.120
Someone is going to ask you
what the book is called.

17:02.122 --> 17:03.788
You should think
of a title now...
- I...

17:03.790 --> 17:05.356
so you don't have
to worry about it later.

17:05.358 --> 17:07.825
I'm fine.
I think on my feet.

17:07.827 --> 17:10.161
Okay.

17:10.163 --> 17:13.798
"Mr. Hollywood."

17:13.800 --> 17:16.701
I'm sorry. What?

17:16.703 --> 17:18.970
Just an idea.

17:18.972 --> 17:20.872
For a title?

17:20.874 --> 17:22.740
Yeah, in case
- You can't think of one later.

17:22.742 --> 17:25.376
I think...
I think it's pretty good.

17:25.378 --> 17:29.547
"Mr. Hollywood."

17:29.549 --> 17:32.050
I-I need another Negroni.

17:32.052 --> 17:34.919
Mm.
Yeah, no shit.

17:37.890 --> 17:41.259
[ Knock on door ]

17:41.261 --> 17:44.028
[ Indistinct conversation ]

17:44.030 --> 17:45.430
[ Conversation stops ]

17:47.232 --> 17:48.933
Hi!

17:48.935 --> 17:50.935
[ Chuckles ]

17:52.371 --> 17:55.106
[ Gasps ] Oh, mijo!

17:55.108 --> 17:57.842
[ Laughing ] Mijo!

17:57.844 --> 18:00.611
Oh, my God.

18:00.613 --> 18:04.515
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

18:06.752 --> 18:08.486
Mijo.

18:14.426 --> 18:15.927
[ Laughter ]

18:15.929 --> 18:17.528
Whoo!

18:24.703 --> 18:27.905
Carlos.
- [ Laughs ]

18:27.907 --> 18:31.642
♪♪

18:51.930 --> 18:53.231
Oscar: Javier.

18:53.233 --> 18:55.099
¿Si, Papa?

18:55.101 --> 18:59.070
Aren't you going to introduce me
to that white person?

18:59.072 --> 19:00.438
Yeah, of course.

19:00.440 --> 19:02.607
Uh, Letty. Hi.

19:02.609 --> 19:03.975
I'm sorry.
This is Letty.

19:03.977 --> 19:05.343
She's, uh, my girlfriend.

19:05.345 --> 19:06.811
Hi.

19:06.813 --> 19:09.847
Oh. Hi.

19:09.849 --> 19:13.284
Drunk already.

19:13.286 --> 19:14.986
Charming.

19:18.190 --> 19:19.657
[ Man singing in Spanish ]

19:19.659 --> 19:21.425
David:
We hear you're a writer.

19:21.427 --> 19:22.927
She's writing a book!

19:22.929 --> 19:24.362
Writing is just a hobby.

19:24.364 --> 19:25.963
You should never give up
your passions.

19:25.965 --> 19:27.465
What's the book about?

19:27.467 --> 19:30.001
It's really more of
a Word document at this point.

19:30.003 --> 19:31.636
What's the Word document about?

19:31.638 --> 19:35.540
A guy who tries to cash in on
his resemblance to Ryan Gosling.

19:35.542 --> 19:37.808
Ryan Gosling.
Who is this?

19:37.810 --> 19:40.378
Oh, he's very famous.
Very famous.

19:40.380 --> 19:42.847
Ryan Gosling
- Is my celebrity free pass.

19:42.849 --> 19:44.282
[ Chuckles ] Your what?

19:44.284 --> 19:46.450
The one celebrity
- I'm allowed to sleep with

19:46.452 --> 19:48.486
if the opportunity
comes up. [ Laughs ]

19:48.488 --> 19:51.289
What's wrong with you?
Huh?

19:51.291 --> 19:53.224
So, what's this guy's name,

19:53.226 --> 19:54.792
the one
who looks like Ryan Gosling?

19:54.794 --> 19:57.795
Lance. He works a hamburger
place called White Castle.

19:57.797 --> 19:59.797
Lance in a White Castle.

19:59.799 --> 20:02.033
Can I read it?
It's a work in progress.

20:02.035 --> 20:03.201
Well, when you finish it, then?

20:03.203 --> 20:04.902
It'll take a long time.

20:04.904 --> 20:06.871
I have a really big job
at Instagram.

20:06.873 --> 20:08.306
The Internet?

20:08.308 --> 20:11.142
It's on the outskirts
of the Internet, yeah.

20:11.144 --> 20:12.510
What do you do?

20:12.512 --> 20:14.078
I assist the local government.

20:14.080 --> 20:15.580
I'm also on the outskirts.

20:15.582 --> 20:17.348
So mysterious.
- Thank you.

20:17.350 --> 20:18.983
Reminds me of your brother.

20:18.985 --> 20:21.385
When I first met him,
I had no idea what he did,

20:21.387 --> 20:24.655
and then I found
all his knives.

20:24.657 --> 20:27.158
And then
I realized he was a chef.

20:27.160 --> 20:28.659
[ Chuckles ]

20:28.661 --> 20:30.695
Speaking of.
I need to get back to it.

20:30.697 --> 20:32.597
Okay.

20:36.902 --> 20:39.403
[ Knife chopping ]

21:14.806 --> 21:16.374
Si.

21:52.978 --> 21:55.746
♪♪

21:57.416 --> 21:59.850
[ Indistinct conversations ]

22:06.258 --> 22:08.025
[ Speaking Spanish ]

22:08.027 --> 22:09.827
Hi.
- Hey.

22:09.829 --> 22:12.697
You okay?
[ Glass clinking ]

22:12.699 --> 22:14.265
Yeah. Are you?
- Yeah.

22:14.267 --> 22:18.536
I'm so happy our family
is all here in my restaurant

22:18.538 --> 22:21.138
that I named
after our birthplace.

22:21.140 --> 22:22.873
In this restaurant

22:22.875 --> 22:25.910
that you so generously
helped me build, Papa.

22:26.678 --> 22:28.279
[ Laughing ] Thank you!

22:28.281 --> 22:30.114
It's a dream come true,

22:30.116 --> 22:33.784
but the bigger dream...
and until last week

22:33.786 --> 22:35.853
I really didn't know
if this would happen...

22:35.855 --> 22:38.956
is that we are all together,
finally,

22:38.958 --> 22:42.893
after much too long,
with Javier.

22:45.063 --> 22:46.297
- Salud.
- Cheers.

22:46.299 --> 22:48.966
Okay.
Oh, I-I almost forgot.

22:48.968 --> 22:53.971
What a wonderful surprise it is
for everyone to meet Letty.

22:53.973 --> 22:55.740
I just love you.

22:55.742 --> 22:57.308
Welcome to the family.

22:57.310 --> 22:59.810
- Cheers.
- Salud.

22:59.812 --> 23:01.379
Salud.
[ Glasses clinking ]

23:01.980 --> 23:04.014
Ava:
Papa, you can't smoke in here.

23:04.016 --> 23:05.316
Mnh-mnh.

23:05.318 --> 23:08.052
[ Lighter clicks ]

23:09.321 --> 23:10.788
For the ash.

23:13.658 --> 23:14.825
So, what is that, Javier?

23:14.827 --> 23:17.628
[ Indistinct conversations ]

23:20.098 --> 23:21.832
Hey, congratulations.

23:21.834 --> 23:24.101
Oscar:
I also have something to say.

23:25.237 --> 23:29.106
Many of us haven't seen each
other for a long, long time.

23:29.108 --> 23:33.611
And it may surprise some of you
that it weighed on me heavily.

23:33.613 --> 23:39.250
I'm not the type
to emote unnecessarily.

23:39.252 --> 23:41.018
But I have to say...

23:41.020 --> 23:44.388
This is one of
the happiest moments of my life.

23:44.390 --> 23:46.123
Bravo, Papa.
Bravo.

23:46.125 --> 23:48.259
[ Woman chuckles ]
- Salud.

23:48.261 --> 23:49.360
All: Salud.

23:49.362 --> 23:51.595
I'm not finished.

23:55.801 --> 24:02.473
"Any life, no matter
how long and complex it may be,

24:02.475 --> 24:04.608
is made out of a single moment.

24:04.610 --> 24:09.713
A moment when a man
finds out once and for all

24:09.715 --> 24:12.149
who he really is."

24:12.151 --> 24:16.120
Argentina's greatest writer
said that.

24:16.122 --> 24:17.221
Who was it?

24:17.223 --> 24:18.556
Do you care, Carlos?

24:18.558 --> 24:21.325
I guess not.
No.

24:21.327 --> 24:23.727
Carlos, can I borrow your son?

24:23.729 --> 24:26.130
For what?
- Tomasito, come.

24:26.132 --> 24:29.033
Come here.

24:33.071 --> 24:38.609
When Javier was 16 years old,
he was a wild kid...

24:38.611 --> 24:43.414
motorcycles, hunting, girls.

24:43.416 --> 24:45.583
But he always had a temper

24:45.585 --> 24:48.919
with his two brothers
David and Carlos.

24:48.921 --> 24:52.590
The only time
that Javier was affectionate

24:52.592 --> 24:54.091
was with little Santino.

24:54.093 --> 24:55.926
Here we go.

24:55.928 --> 24:57.595
[ Sighs ]

24:57.597 --> 25:00.297
Who's Santino?

25:00.299 --> 25:02.933
Papa, please.

25:02.935 --> 25:05.302
When the family's all together,

25:05.304 --> 25:08.105
it's important to recognize
the ones who are not.

25:08.107 --> 25:09.273
Okay.

25:09.275 --> 25:13.444
Little Santino
was the youngest, the baby,

25:13.446 --> 25:16.146
and Javier loved him
very, very much.

25:16.148 --> 25:20.484
He taught him how to fish,
how to cook.

25:20.486 --> 25:23.454
On little Santino's
7th birthday,

25:23.456 --> 25:28.192
Javier wanted to take him for
a camping trip to Gran Chaco.

25:28.194 --> 25:30.294
So they found
one of the old Jeeps

25:30.296 --> 25:33.898
laying around the property,
and off they went.

25:33.900 --> 25:38.802
They were supposed to stay up
until midnight for his birthday,

25:38.804 --> 25:42.873
but little Santino
never made it to midnight.

25:45.410 --> 25:47.645
How did it start again?

25:47.647 --> 25:51.849
I was teaching Santino
how to start a fire.

25:51.851 --> 25:54.051
Teach him how to start a fire.

25:54.053 --> 25:55.386
To a 7-year-old.

25:55.388 --> 25:59.657
Well, little Santino might not
have adhered very closely

25:59.659 --> 26:01.992
to Javier's instruction...

26:01.994 --> 26:05.229
because something that he did

26:05.231 --> 26:07.598
caused Javier
to throw a rock at his head.

26:07.600 --> 26:10.167
It was not a rock.

26:10.169 --> 26:13.504
It was a small stone.
Almost a pebble.

26:13.506 --> 26:16.874
Santino was dancing around
with a torch

26:16.876 --> 26:19.343
near the dry brush.

26:19.345 --> 26:22.880
He almost started
a forest fire for miles.

26:22.882 --> 26:27.184
So to save his precious forest,

26:27.186 --> 26:32.423
Javier threw a rock
at his little brother's head.

26:32.425 --> 26:34.858
[ Thump, woman gasps ]

26:36.294 --> 26:37.761
Just like that.

26:40.565 --> 26:42.433
Santino said he was fine.

26:42.435 --> 26:45.235
I'm sure he said he was fine.

26:45.237 --> 26:48.439
But then he got tired,
didn't he?

26:48.441 --> 26:49.807
He wanted to lie down.

26:49.809 --> 26:53.243
And what do you do
with a head injury?

26:53.245 --> 26:55.746
I didn't know.

26:55.748 --> 26:57.881
Javier said, "You go lay down.

26:57.883 --> 27:02.086
I'll wake you up at midnight
for your birthday."

27:02.088 --> 27:05.189
So little Santino
went right to sleep.

27:09.394 --> 27:13.797
When your brain starts to lose
blood, you get drowsy first.

27:13.799 --> 27:18.002
Always keep someone
with a head injury awake,

27:18.004 --> 27:23.607
because the next morning,
on his 7th birthday,

27:23.609 --> 27:26.577
little Santino did not wake up.

27:26.579 --> 27:32.116
Javier went to sleep and forgot
to wake him up at midnight.

27:32.118 --> 27:35.619
He let him sleep
all night long.

27:35.621 --> 27:39.923
And before checking on him
again, he went fishing.

27:39.925 --> 27:41.492
He made a pot of coffee

27:41.494 --> 27:44.128
while Santino lay dead
inside of a sleeping bag.

27:44.130 --> 27:45.796
[ Crying ] It wasn't his fault.

27:45.798 --> 27:47.798
He was only 16 years old.

27:47.800 --> 27:49.099
He knew better.

27:49.101 --> 27:50.768
He couldn't have saved him.

27:50.770 --> 27:53.103
Yes, he could have saved him.
You know this.

27:53.105 --> 27:55.973
I spoke to a doctor.
He was very clear.

27:55.975 --> 27:59.777
They would detected the brain
injury with a CAT scan.

27:59.779 --> 28:01.679
They could have
preformed surgery.

28:01.681 --> 28:04.314
How many doctors did you ask

28:04.316 --> 28:06.483
before you found one
that told you that?

28:06.485 --> 28:10.621
He would be alive today
if it weren't for you.

28:10.623 --> 28:13.791
I'm certain of that.

28:13.793 --> 28:15.693
I am sorry.

28:15.695 --> 28:18.162
Of course you're sorry.
You killed your little brother.

28:18.164 --> 28:21.832
It makes sense to be sorry.

28:21.834 --> 28:24.301
Are you done?

28:24.303 --> 28:25.669
Yes.

28:25.671 --> 28:28.872
I think I am, now that we have
remembered little Santino.

28:29.974 --> 28:35.546
Thank you for listening
to an old man talk.

28:35.548 --> 28:38.949
To Santino.

28:47.559 --> 28:49.326
[ Sighs ]

28:54.199 --> 28:56.333
[ Squishing ]

28:56.335 --> 28:59.369
[ Sizzling ]

28:59.371 --> 29:02.773
♪♪

29:05.877 --> 29:07.578
I think we should go.

29:07.580 --> 29:09.279
No.

29:09.281 --> 29:10.881
Was your father
always like that?

29:10.883 --> 29:14.384
I'm serious.
I think we should go.

29:14.386 --> 29:16.120
No.

29:16.122 --> 29:19.089
You're telling me that
what just happened was okay?

29:19.091 --> 29:21.959
Obviously what happened to
your brother was not your fault.

29:21.961 --> 29:23.560
How was it not my fault?

29:23.562 --> 29:25.229
I hit him in the head.
He died from the injury.

29:25.231 --> 29:26.730
That is what happened.

29:26.732 --> 29:31.135
I know my father is...
who he is,

29:31.137 --> 29:32.436
but he's right about that.

29:32.438 --> 29:33.904
You see,
- This is why we should go.

29:33.906 --> 29:35.839
You can go.

29:39.778 --> 29:42.246
[ Knife thuds ]
- Just go!

29:42.248 --> 29:43.947
Please.

29:46.651 --> 29:50.754
You guys, what's
- Going on with this family.

29:50.756 --> 29:52.256
What is that?

29:52.258 --> 29:54.291
Nothing.
[ Chuckles ]

29:54.293 --> 29:56.026
Show me.

29:59.731 --> 30:02.666
Are you seriously
- Huffing ether right now?

30:02.668 --> 30:04.635
The only time I've ever
heard of anyone doing this

30:04.637 --> 30:05.736
was in "Fear and Loathing."

30:05.738 --> 30:07.271
That's where we got it.

30:07.273 --> 30:10.274
We needed to kill some major
brain cells after that insanity.

30:10.276 --> 30:12.276
Promise not to tell,
Aunt Letty.

30:12.278 --> 30:14.845
Don't ever call me that again.

30:14.847 --> 30:16.079
Okay.

30:16.081 --> 30:17.447
You want to try it?

30:17.449 --> 30:20.150
I'm not doing ether
with two teenage girls.

30:20.152 --> 30:21.618
Is that how you see us?

30:21.620 --> 30:24.621
After "The Ballad of Little
Santino," how could you not?

30:24.623 --> 30:27.090
Has Uncle Jav
ever told you that story?

30:27.092 --> 30:28.325
Um, no.

30:28.327 --> 30:30.994
We found out
- A couple years ago. It's sad.

30:30.996 --> 30:33.997
I mean, what the hell is wrong
with your grandfather's brain?

30:33.999 --> 30:35.632
You know when people say,

30:35.634 --> 30:37.301
"My grandpa's
from another generation,"

30:37.303 --> 30:39.803
and it means
- That he's racist or sexist?

30:39.805 --> 30:40.871
Yeah.

30:40.873 --> 30:42.940
Well, in Argentina
when you say that,

30:42.942 --> 30:45.342
it means that he killed
a lot of people in the '70s.

30:45.344 --> 30:47.477
[ Chuckles ]
I'm sorry. What?

30:47.479 --> 30:51.181
Go to Wikipedia
- And put in the "Dirty War."

30:56.521 --> 30:58.789
Holy shit.

30:58.791 --> 31:00.457
Oscar was involved in this?

31:00.459 --> 31:03.293
He wasn't, like,
in charge of it, but...

31:03.295 --> 31:05.796
It says tens of thousands
of people were killed.

31:05.798 --> 31:08.665
Whenever we ask about it,
they just say it was politics.

31:08.667 --> 31:11.535
Super-sketch.

31:11.537 --> 31:14.705
Girls, come inside.

31:24.916 --> 31:26.850
[ Can sprays ]

31:26.852 --> 31:28.051
[ Sniffs ]

31:28.053 --> 31:30.120
Oh, that's gross.

31:33.224 --> 31:36.460
♪♪

31:51.376 --> 31:52.776
[ Man singing in Spanish ]

31:52.778 --> 31:54.711
Conchita: [ Laughs ]
Come in.

31:54.713 --> 31:56.013
Okay.

31:57.548 --> 31:59.016
Would you mind terribly

31:59.018 --> 32:01.551
if I switched places with you
at the dinner table?

32:01.553 --> 32:03.453
You don't want
to sit next to Javier?

32:03.455 --> 32:04.922
I see him every day.

32:04.924 --> 32:06.523
I'm sure
- You'd love to sit next to him.

32:06.525 --> 32:08.191
Are you sure?

32:08.193 --> 32:10.761
Absolutely.

32:10.763 --> 32:14.798
[ Singing in Spanish continues ]

32:29.747 --> 32:33.817
[ Indistinct conversations ]

32:35.920 --> 32:37.988
So, how do you feel
about knocking that little boy

32:37.990 --> 32:39.723
in the head
with your fist earlier?

32:39.725 --> 32:41.925
How do I feel about it?

32:41.927 --> 32:43.226
Yeah.

32:43.228 --> 32:44.728
It's pretty traumatic.

32:44.730 --> 32:46.630
Maybe you should say
you're sorry.

32:46.632 --> 32:49.666
You want me
- To apologize to a child?

32:49.668 --> 32:52.970
Maybe you should apologize
to your son.

32:52.972 --> 32:54.938
Javier?

32:54.940 --> 32:56.840
What for?

32:56.842 --> 32:59.276
Because he didn't know
what to do about a head wound.

32:59.278 --> 33:00.477
He was a kid.

33:00.479 --> 33:02.112
He was 16.

33:02.114 --> 33:05.282
Do you think that maybe you
could have consoled him

33:05.284 --> 33:07.417
instead of kicking him out
of your family?

33:07.419 --> 33:09.086
Oh, you'll fit right in.

33:09.088 --> 33:10.620
Is that right?

33:10.622 --> 33:13.757
Let me tell you
how this family works.

33:13.759 --> 33:18.362
Everyone's on Javier's side,

33:18.364 --> 33:21.932
and I'm left alone to look
like a spiteful old man.

33:21.934 --> 33:24.534
[ Chuckles ] Aren't you?

33:24.536 --> 33:26.536
I'm glad
everyone's enjoying themselves.

33:26.538 --> 33:29.106
- Yeah.
- Everything is perfect.

33:29.108 --> 33:30.107
Silk: Mm-hmm.

33:30.109 --> 33:31.775
I'll be right back
with dessert.

33:31.777 --> 33:35.045
[ Indistinct conversations ]

33:36.714 --> 33:39.082
Gracias, Soledad.

33:41.819 --> 33:44.121
Do you love him?

33:45.289 --> 33:46.990
I'm not sure yet.

33:46.992 --> 33:50.694
Well, we're about to find out.

33:59.704 --> 34:02.005
[ Thunder crashes ]

34:02.007 --> 34:04.541
[ Indistinct conversations ]

34:13.551 --> 34:15.952
♪♪

34:38.376 --> 34:40.911
I'm 15, and Sofia's 16.

34:40.913 --> 34:42.446
We're not children.

34:42.448 --> 34:43.980
Go.

34:56.194 --> 34:58.562
That's better.

34:58.564 --> 35:00.263
Now we can all be real people.

35:00.265 --> 35:02.532
Yes. Good.

35:02.534 --> 35:04.868
Been wanting to know why you had
to hit my son on the head.

35:04.870 --> 35:06.236
It's good for him.

35:06.238 --> 35:08.805
It toughens him up.

35:10.074 --> 35:13.076
So, Javier...

35:13.078 --> 35:14.544
Yes?

35:14.546 --> 35:16.613
I bet you can't wait
to get out of here.

35:16.615 --> 35:19.382
You know,
- You're not wrong about that.

35:19.384 --> 35:23.253
Papa, I think
some of us were misled

35:23.255 --> 35:25.255
as to why you wanted to visit.

35:25.257 --> 35:27.290
How can you say that?

35:27.292 --> 35:29.559
I wanted to see
this beautiful restaurant.

35:29.561 --> 35:32.462
My only daughter's dream
coming true.

35:32.464 --> 35:33.730
But you also said you wanted

35:33.732 --> 35:35.799
to make things right
with Javier.

35:35.801 --> 35:36.900
And I do.

35:36.902 --> 35:38.635
Doesn't seem like you do.

35:38.637 --> 35:40.103
I'm sorry you feel that way.

35:40.105 --> 35:42.239
But let's see what else
I have to say, huh?

35:42.241 --> 35:44.341
[ Sighs ]

35:44.343 --> 35:46.476
It's been so many years.

35:46.478 --> 35:50.080
There's so little
I know about my son.

35:50.082 --> 35:51.348
Like, for instance,

35:51.350 --> 35:53.617
what are you doing
for a living these days?

35:53.619 --> 35:56.486
You know what I do.
We've talked about this.

35:56.488 --> 35:58.021
Oh, yeah, yeah.

35:58.023 --> 36:00.290
I know you cook well enough

36:00.292 --> 36:05.629
to let everybody
believe you're a chef,

36:05.631 --> 36:08.899
but is that all you do
to make ends meet?

36:12.870 --> 36:14.638
Yes.

36:14.640 --> 36:16.640
That's not quite true, is it?

36:16.642 --> 36:19.976
In fact, I was so curious
about what my son was doing,

36:19.978 --> 36:21.878
and not being able
to contact him,

36:21.880 --> 36:26.583
I had David hire someone
to check into it.

36:31.622 --> 36:37.561
Why do you disrespect this
family by lying to our faces?

36:41.399 --> 36:44.701
Darling, I'm sorry to be
the one to tell you this,

36:44.703 --> 36:49.439
but your beloved son
is a contract killer.

36:51.175 --> 36:53.543
[ Laughs ]

36:53.545 --> 36:55.645
I'm sorry for my husband.

36:55.647 --> 36:58.381
He always had
a sick sense of humor.

36:58.383 --> 36:59.883
[ Laughs ]
- Did you know this?

36:59.885 --> 37:02.419
About your sick sense of humor?

37:02.421 --> 37:04.888
Yeah, I picked up on that
pretty quickly.

37:04.890 --> 37:06.656
Nah.

37:06.658 --> 37:08.825
Do you know
- What your boyfriend does

37:08.827 --> 37:11.928
when he goes
on his little trips?

37:11.930 --> 37:14.564
He's a private chef.

37:14.566 --> 37:17.067
I think we should go.

37:17.069 --> 37:19.069
I agree.
Let's go.

37:19.071 --> 37:20.604
Do you know this guy?

37:21.505 --> 37:23.006
He died of a heart attack.

37:23.008 --> 37:26.576
Uh, he looks
- In pretty good shape to me.

37:28.746 --> 37:33.049
This woman...
She fell in the shower.

37:33.051 --> 37:36.086
The coroner said
that it was an accident.

37:36.088 --> 37:38.355
[ Sniffs ] Too bad.

37:38.357 --> 37:41.891
Ah, this guy
died of natural causes.

37:41.893 --> 37:45.762
Perhaps not so natural, huh?

37:45.764 --> 37:48.798
Who are these people?
What's happening?

37:48.800 --> 37:53.103
Maybe Papa didn't have
a heart attack, Ma.

37:53.105 --> 37:54.471
I think it was a stroke.

37:56.741 --> 37:58.775
Be a man and tell the truth!

37:58.777 --> 38:00.110
Tell your mother
and your sister

38:00.112 --> 38:03.480
and your brothers
and little girlfriend!

38:04.782 --> 38:07.550
Tell them so I don't have
to listen to them

38:07.552 --> 38:11.621
begging me to let you
back into the family.

38:11.623 --> 38:14.958
I always knew,
and now they all know.

38:14.960 --> 38:19.129
You were a killer at 16,
and you're a killer now.

38:20.498 --> 38:22.632
You're evil.

38:22.634 --> 38:26.036
And if you don't tell
the truth, Silk will!

38:30.908 --> 38:32.075
Tell them!

38:32.077 --> 38:35.345
I have nothing to say.
Sure, you do.

38:35.347 --> 38:36.680
Leave him alone.

38:36.682 --> 38:39.416
Come on, tell them.

38:39.418 --> 38:42.652
I don't know
what you're talking about.

38:43.854 --> 38:45.188
[ Gun cocks ]
Ava: David!

38:45.190 --> 38:46.823
Oh!
- David!

38:48.259 --> 38:49.259
Talk.

38:49.261 --> 38:51.828
David, put down the gun!

38:51.830 --> 38:53.363
[ Gasps ]

38:53.365 --> 38:55.131
Put it down!

38:55.133 --> 38:57.334
What is going on?

38:57.336 --> 38:58.768
[ Crying ]

38:58.770 --> 39:00.503
I will tell the truth...

39:00.505 --> 39:04.708
after you put down the gun.

39:10.681 --> 39:12.649
♪♪

39:12.651 --> 39:16.720
David, put down the gun!

39:25.796 --> 39:28.631
Javier, what is this?

39:28.633 --> 39:32.202
How many people did<i> you</i> kill?

39:32.204 --> 39:34.637
Unh-unh.
This is not about me.

39:34.639 --> 39:36.673
That's what all of this
is about.

39:36.675 --> 39:39.809
You sit there
accusing me of murder,

39:39.811 --> 39:41.177
when you are responsible

39:41.179 --> 39:43.413
for killing thousands
of innocent people!

39:58.829 --> 40:00.663
Aah!
- Conchita: Stop!

40:02.199 --> 40:04.667
What are you doing?

40:04.669 --> 40:08.271
Javier's about to kill
another one of your sons.

40:10.674 --> 40:13.009
[ Bullet thuds ]

40:13.011 --> 40:17.447
You forced me out of my family.

40:17.449 --> 40:19.182
You left me with no one.

40:19.184 --> 40:20.884
I was invisible.

40:20.886 --> 40:24.287
Because of you, I've been
totally alone since I was a kid.

40:24.289 --> 40:26.723
Not because of me.

40:26.725 --> 40:28.925
Because of you.

40:30.761 --> 40:32.796
If it weren't for Ava...

40:34.765 --> 40:38.735
I am here tonight
because Ava told me

40:38.737 --> 40:42.238
that I could have
my family back.

40:42.240 --> 40:45.742
All of the beautiful people
in this room.

40:45.744 --> 40:47.577
And I thought
if there was a chance

40:47.579 --> 40:49.579
that you would
let me back in...

40:49.581 --> 40:52.549
[Voice breaking] if you
would really forgive me...

40:54.485 --> 40:58.054
then I would forgive you.

40:58.056 --> 41:01.424
I don't need forgiveness
for anything.

41:01.426 --> 41:03.393
[ Breathes sharply ]

41:12.336 --> 41:16.673
I will never see you again.

41:19.243 --> 41:23.513
Well, finally,
we agree on one thing.

41:31.088 --> 41:32.188
[ Gasping ]

41:32.190 --> 41:34.123
Well...

41:34.125 --> 41:36.726
is everybody ready to go?

41:43.133 --> 41:44.968
Yes?

41:44.970 --> 41:47.504
My ice cream has melted.

41:47.506 --> 41:49.772
So?
I'll go get the little ones.

41:49.774 --> 41:52.408
Stay, Mama.
I'll go get them.

41:54.044 --> 41:55.545
Find the girls.

41:56.547 --> 41:59.549
Why isn't
everybody standing up?!

42:13.631 --> 42:14.831
Ava.

42:14.833 --> 42:18.034
Are you
- Coming with your family?

42:18.036 --> 42:20.336
Or are you staying with Javier?

42:20.338 --> 42:22.872
Poor Javier.
Like always.

42:24.742 --> 42:27.677
I'm not going anywhere
with you.

42:27.679 --> 42:31.714
Well,
- As one of your investors,

42:31.716 --> 42:34.150
I recommend switching chefs,

42:34.152 --> 42:38.521
because the meat was overdone
and the peaches were burnt.

42:38.523 --> 42:43.493
Other than that,
- It's a beautiful restaurant.

42:43.495 --> 42:46.062
You're welcome.

42:49.934 --> 42:52.769
What is going on?

42:52.771 --> 42:54.070
Someone will explain it to you.

42:54.072 --> 42:57.874
Or I will explain it to you...

42:57.876 --> 42:59.776
one day.

43:12.356 --> 43:14.958
I'll be in the kitchen.

43:27.805 --> 43:29.639
Is it true?

43:32.610 --> 43:35.678
You're not a private chef?

43:46.890 --> 43:49.025
No.

43:58.502 --> 44:00.236
Look, I got into this life
because...

44:00.238 --> 44:01.838
What life?!

44:01.840 --> 44:04.340
A life
- Of ending other people's lives?

44:04.342 --> 44:05.575
Yeah, but these people,
they're not...

44:05.577 --> 44:08.878
Not what? Innocent?

44:14.618 --> 44:17.987
You kill people?

44:19.990 --> 44:22.425
No, you don't.

44:22.427 --> 44:26.029
I know you don't do this.

44:44.448 --> 44:46.883
[ Sniffles ]

44:46.885 --> 44:48.918
[ Sighs ]

44:55.492 --> 45:00.063
You believed him
- When he said you were a killer

45:00.065 --> 45:01.497
when you were 16.

45:01.499 --> 45:04.167
[ Sniffles ]

45:04.169 --> 45:05.401
Ava...

45:05.403 --> 45:08.738
And he turned you into this.

45:18.582 --> 45:21.584
Ay.
[ Breathes deeply ]

45:21.586 --> 45:24.253
Oh. [ Sniffles ]

45:33.897 --> 45:35.765
No.

46:00.190 --> 46:02.792
[ Sniffles ]

46:13.403 --> 46:16.739
Ava.

46:16.741 --> 46:19.842
Ava.

46:24.915 --> 46:27.316
[ Sniffles ]

46:30.254 --> 46:32.722
[ Sighs ]

46:32.724 --> 46:34.991
[ Footsteps approaching ]

46:43.133 --> 46:46.903
Go.
Please... go.

46:46.905 --> 46:49.071
I'm not going anywhere.

46:51.308 --> 46:53.643
Here.
[ Sniffles ]

46:53.645 --> 46:55.244
Take the car.
I don't need it.

47:02.119 --> 47:05.188
Okay.

47:05.190 --> 47:06.622
I will.

47:06.624 --> 47:09.292
[ Breathes deeply ]

47:09.294 --> 47:11.894
And I'll take you.

47:19.636 --> 47:21.938
[ Sniffles ]

47:23.941 --> 47:27.677
[ Sobs ]

47:37.354 --> 47:40.923
♪♪
